{
  "stem": "26728.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Did you hook me back up?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I think we were discussing my revisit to Fort Sill, Oklahoma where I went for what they call liaison pilot training.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And this was in early 1943.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "One of the thing is that I'll never forget-- having been to Fort Sill before, and having been to Texas before-- I got very accustomed to their Country Western music, which we just call Texican music.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And-- and also, having been from Tucson, Arizona, which was not nearly as Country Western as Texas or Oklahoma, the song that used to drive us all nuts both in 1940, 1941, and still in 1943 was the 'Yellow Rose of Texas.'",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "'San Antonio Rose.' OK, 'San Antonio Rose.' This started in the-- in 1940.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I'll just do a little.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Excuse me.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I lost my voice 50 years ago, but it-- it's [SINGING] Deep within my heart lies a melody, a song of old San Anton.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that goes on and on about-- about San Antonio Rose.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I think that's all I can remember.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It's a real pretty song.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But you know, every radio station had that sucker on all the time.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So anyhow, I finished my flight training at Fort Sill, became-- got my wings as-- as an [?",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "L-pilot, ?] went back to Camp Adair.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The unit then moved-- the whole-- our division, the 70th division, moved to Fort Leonard Wood, Missouri in the summer-- well, it was the same year, 1943-- late-- later in '43.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Now, Fort Leonard Wood is a military-- a regular fort military post, been there for many, many years.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It's up in the Ozark mountains about 60 miles from St.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Louis.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "A good fort, a good post.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "We had-- we had nice barracks.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "It was really very, very pleasant.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
